column3: and public educational center focusing on the social and economic causes of world hunger. Investigates the root causes of hunger and food problems in the U.S. and abroad. Aims to transform the American economic system into a democratic order where all citizens can participate in planning for the well-being of others and everyone can benefit equitably from their labor. Works to cut through popular myths about hunger using radio and television
column5: and publications. Seeks to find appropriate responses to world hunger. Helps people weigh alternative long-term strategies to end hunger and build networks of progressive groups worldwide by contacting people in all parts of the world who are working to end hunger in their countries."***Narratives*2

4225818*Narratives*Narrative text*"Educational and activist group that opposes all forms of animal exploitation. Seeks to educate the public against speciesism and human chauvinist attitudes toward animals through documentary films
column3: and pictures of current conditions in slaughterhouses and animal experimentation laboratories. Conducts rallies and demonstrations to focus attention on the four major institutionalized cruelty issues: the exploitation and abuse of animals in experimentation
column5: abuse of animals in the entertainment industry
column6: and slaughtering for human consumption. Offers children's services; conducts research and charitable programs; compiles statistics; maintains speakers' bureau. Provides low-cost spaying and neutering for local dogs and cats
column7: free doghouses to locals with backyard dogs; provides hands-on rescue of local animals; provides services for students; maintains a print and an audio-visual library
column8: and will provide information or other literature to the public."***Narratives*2

column1: 12188772*Narratives*Narrative text*"Dedicated to the standardization of ordering and fulfillment within the book industry and to the development of computer-to-computer communications between the purchaser and the vendor
column2: as well as between publishers and their suppliers. Its activities include promoting the use of machine-readable coding on books; publicizing the correct use of the International Standard Book Number (ISBN) by publishers and their customers; developing computer-to-computer ordering
column5: and other formats; recommending telecommunications protocols; providing liaison with other endeavors directed toward establishing national standards for the technical aspects of retail trade; and developing a meaningful system for scanning books at point of sale for inventory taking and in returns processing."***Narratives*4
